! conclusion: Current institutional reality distorts several of the Role × Value invariants. [👓/们 🌱/己]

  + IF: The Role × Value invariants are projected into actual institutional behaviour.

  + HOWEVER: Current institutional reality distorts several of these invariants — metadata rigidity, opaque embargo management, siloed reuse signals, and manual entry with inconsistent support.

  + THEN: Operate an explicit move on the named axis (see substructure below); steward the pattern against the declared discipline.

The projection of institutional identity into actual behaviour
                 reveals the productive tensions that Slide 3’s transformation
                 pattern must address.

  + because: Plural visibility is only partially realised.

  + because: Trust surfaces are inconsistently expressed.

  + because: Interoperability is constrained by system architecture.

  + because: Contribution friction remains high for many depositors.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    + Realise plural visibility more fully across stakeholder groups.
    + Make trust surfaces consistently expressed.
    + Relax the system-architecture constraints on interoperability.
    + Lower contribution friction for depositors.
    + Address the productive tensions that Slide 3's transformation pattern must resolve.
